@Node "List Options" "pro.guide/List Options"

List Options
............

@{b}List Macro Expansion@{ub}
     If this gadget is selected, the complete macro text for all macro
     expansions is included in the listing.  See @{"OPT M" Link "pro.guide/OPT LIST"}.

@{b}List Macro Definitions@{ub}
     Macro definitions are included in the listing when this gadget is
     selected.  See @{"OPT MD" Link "pro.guide/OPT LIST"}.

@{b}List Symbol Table@{ub}
     By selecting this gadget you tell the assembler to add a symbol
     listing to the listing file.  See @{"Symbol listing" Link "Symbol listing"}.

@{b}List Include Files@{ub}
     The contents of included files is included in the listing when
     this gadget is selected (see @{"FORMAT" Link "pro.guide/FORMAT"}).

@{b}List Conditional Directives@{ub}
     Select this gadget to include conditional assembly directives in
     the listing file (see @{"OPT CL" Link "pro.guide/OPT LIST"}).

@{b}No Listing Header@{ub}
     This gadget can be used to suppress all titles and subtitles.  See
     @{"FORMAT" Link "pro.guide/FORMAT"}, for more information.

@{b}No Line Numbers@{ub}
     If this gadget is selected, no line numbers are written to the
     listing.  See @{"FORMAT" Link "pro.guide/FORMAT"}.

@{b}No Section# and Offset@{ub}
     The section numbering and program counter offset are suppressed
     when this gadget is selected (see @{"FORMAT" Link "pro.guide/FORMAT"}).

@{b}Bytes Opcode Dump@{ub}
     This cycle-gadget allows you to specify the width of the hexdump
     field in bytes.  The range of the width is from 2-22 bytes, or @{b}No@{ub}
     to suppress the hexdump field completely.  See @{"FORMAT" Link "pro.guide/FORMAT"}.

@{b}PLEN@{ub}
     The @{b}PLEN@{ub} integer-gadget can be used to set the page length for the
     assembly listing.  The page length may be a value between 12 and
     255.  See @{"PLEN" Link "pro.guide/LLEN"}.

@{b}LLEN@{ub}
     By entering a value into the integer-gadget, you can set the line
     length for the listing.  The line length should be from 38 to 255.
     A value of zero instructs ProOpts not to write the line length to
     the configuration file.  See @{"LLEN" Link "pro.guide/LLEN"}, for more details.

@{b}Listing File@{ub}
     Using the string-gadget you can specify the filename of the
     listing file (see @{"Auxiliary Output Files" Link "pro.guide/Auxiliary Output Files"}).  The name can be set by
     either typing it into the string-gadget, or by using the file
     requester that opened when the @{b}Select@{ub} gadget was pressed.  See
     @{"LISTFILE" Link "pro.guide/LISTFILE"}.

@{b}Listing Title@{ub}
     You can specify a page title by typing it into this string-gadget
     (see @{"TTL" Link "pro.guide/LLEN"}).


@EndNode

@Node "Linker Options" "pro.guide/Linker Options"

Linker Options
..............

@{b}Small Object@{ub}
     Select this gadget when you want to have all hunks merged into one
     single @{b}CODE@{ub} hunk.  See @{"SMALLOBJ" Link "pro.guide/SMALLOBJ"}, for more details.

@{b}Auto XRef@{ub}
     When this gadget is selected, the assembler treats all undefined
     symbols as external symbols (see @{"AUTOXREF" Link "pro.guide/AUTOXREF"}).

@{b}SmallCode@{ub}
     When this check-gadget is selected, all code hunks are merged into
     one single hunk (see @{"SMALLCODE" Link "pro.guide/SMALLOBJ"}).

@{b}SmallData@{ub}
     When this check-gadget is selected, all data hunks are merged into
     one single hunk (see @{"SMALLDATA" Link "pro.guide/SMALLOBJ"}).

@{b}SmallBSS@{ub}
     When this check-gadget is selected, all bss hunks are merged into
     one single hunk (see @{"SMALLBSS" Link "pro.guide/SMALLOBJ"}).

@{b}Debug Symbols@{ub}
     With this cycle-gadget you can particularize the way symbol
     information is written to the object file.  You can choose between:
    @{b}None@{ub}
          for no symbol information,

    @{b}All@{ub}
          when the symbol information for all defined symbols should be
          written to object file (see @{"ADDSYM" Link "pro.guide/Debugging Information"}), or

    @{b}Exports Only@{ub}
          that restricts the symbol information generation to the
          exported (@{b}XDEF@{ub}) symbols only (see @{"OPT X+" Link "pro.guide/Debugging Information"}).

@{b}Line Debug@{ub}
     This gadget allows you to set the format of the debugging
     information.  See @{"DEBUG" Link "pro.guide/Debugging Information"}, for more detailed information, especially
     for the @{b}LINE@{ub} and @{b}HCLN@{ub} keywords.

@{b}Debugging Information@{ub}
     You can specify the type of debugging information to be produced.
     See @{"DEBUG" Link "pro.guide/Debugging Information"}.

@{b}All Includes@{ub}
     When this check-gadget is set, debugging information for all
     included files is generated (see @{"DEBUG" Link "pro.guide/Debugging Information"}, for the @{b}ALL@{ub} keyword).

@{b}Origin@{ub}
     This integer-gadget can be used to set the load address for the
     S-record file (see @{"SREC" Link "pro.guide/SREC"}).

@{b}S-Record Type@{ub}
     This cycle-gadget allows you to set the Motorola Record format
     type for the S-record file.  See @{"SREC" Link "pro.guide/SREC"}.

@{b}Length@{ub}
     You can set the record length of the S-record file by typing the
     value into the integer-gadget.  The value must be from 16 to 255.
     See @{"SREC" Link "pro.guide/SREC"}, for more information.


@EndNode

